{"word":"σκανδάληθρον","slug":"σκανδάληθρον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n94548\" key=\"skanda/lhqron\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"suff\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">σκανδάλ-ηθρον</orth>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">τό</gen>, <sense id=\"n94548.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">stick in a trap</tr_> on which the bait is placed, and which, when touched by the animal, springs up and shuts the trap, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0542.tlg001:7:114\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Poll.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">7.114</biblScope></bibl>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0542.tlg001:10:156\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">10.156</biblScope> </bibl>: metaph., <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">σκανδάληθρ᾽ ἱστὰς ἐπῶν</foreign> setting word-<tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">traps</tr_>, i.e. throwing out words which one's adversary will catch at, and so be caught himself, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0019.tlg001.perseus-grc1:687\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ar.\">Ar.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ach.\">Ach.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">687</biblScope></bibl>, ubi <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">v.</abbr> Sch., cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0434.tlg001:457\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Cratin.</author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">457</biblScope> </bibl>; cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">σκάνδαλον</foreign>.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}